# MCP tool design rules

## Naming

- snake_case verb_noun: `search_farmland`, `get_weather_1km`, `get_pesticide_rules`.
- Avoid vague verbs (`run`, `do`, `query`) and noun-only names (`farmland`).
- Once a tool name appears in a published version (CHANGELOG.md), it is **frozen**. Add a new tool and deprecate.

## Input schema (Zod)

- Required arguments ≤ 3 unless justified.
- Every argument has a `.describe()` written for the LLM, full sentence.
- Use enums for closed sets, `z.number().int().min().max()` for bounded ints.
- Pagination: `limit` (default 20, max 100) and `cursor` (opaque string).
- Use `z.object({...}).strict()` so unknown fields are rejected.

## Visibility

- `model-visible` (default): tools the LLM should consider during reasoning.
- `visibility: ["app"]` (Phase 5): tools called only by the MCP Apps UI; the LLM should not see them.
- Aim for ~7 model-visible tools and ≥7 app-only tools. Too many model-visible tools burns context.

## Side-effect classification

Each tool file exports `meta.sideEffect`:

- `read-only` — safe to call repeatedly; no external irreversible effect.
- `draft` — produces a non-committed artefact; explicit user step needed to commit.
- `mutating` — changes state somewhere; must include audit log + operation id in output.
- `destructive` — deletes / cancels / sends. Two-step (`prepare_*` + `confirm_*`) required.

## Output

- `content` MUST contain at least one `text` entry, written for the LLM (a 1–3 sentence summary).
- `structuredContent` is the machine-readable shape, validated by an output Zod schema.
- For paginated tools, include `next_cursor` in `structuredContent`.
- For UI-driven tools, include `_meta.openWidget = "ui://sugu-agri/<name>.html"` and a textual fallback in `content`.
- Always include the data source attribution (`structuredContent.attribution`) when that is required by the source license.

## Errors

- Validation: `{ isError: true, content: [{ type: "text", text: "Invalid <field>: <reason>" }] }`. Never throw.
- Upstream / not-found / auth: throw a typed error from `src/lib/errors.ts`; the registry layer maps it to a JSON-RPC error.

## Example tool skeleton

```ts
import { z } from "zod";
import type { McpServer } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js";
import type { Deps } from "../server/deps.js";

export const meta = {
  name: "search_farmland",
  sideEffect: "read-only",
  visibility: "model" as const,
};

export const searchFarmlandInputSchema = z
  .object({
    query: z.string().describe("Address, place name, or farm operator name."),
    prefecture: z.string().optional().describe("Two-character prefecture code (e.g. JP-46)."),
    limit: z.number().int().min(1).max(100).default(20),
    cursor: z.string().optional(),
  })
  .strict();

export function registerSearchFarmland(server: McpServer, deps: Deps) {
  server.registerTool(
    "search_farmland",
    {
      title: "Search Japanese farmland",
      description: "Search eMAFF Fude polygons by address, prefecture or operator name. Read-only.",
      inputSchema: searchFarmlandInputSchema.shape,
    },
    async (args) => {
      const parsed = searchFarmlandInputSchema.safeParse(args);
      if (!parsed.success) {
        return {
          isError: true,
          content: [
            { type: "text", text: `Invalid input: ${parsed.error.issues[0]?.message ?? "unknown"}` },
          ],
        };
      }
      const result = await deps.emaff.search(parsed.data);
      return {
        content: [{ type: "text", text: `${result.fields.length} farmland match(es).` }],
        structuredContent: result,
      };
    },
  );
}
```
